Consider the following ANSI C code segment:
z = x + 3 + y->f1 + y->f2;
for (i = 0; i < 200; i = i + 2) {
    if (z > i) {
        p = p + x + 3;
        q = q + y->f1;
    } else {
        p = p + y->f2;
        q = q + (x + 3 + y->f1);
    }
}
Assume that the variable y points to a struct (allocated on the heap) containing two fields f1 and f2, and the local variables x, y, z, p, q, and i are all register allocated. Common sub-expression elimination (CSE) is applied on the code. The number of addition and dereference operations of the form y->f1 and y->f2 in the optimized code respectively are:
A. 403 and 102
B. 303 and 2
C. 503 and 102
D. 303 and 2

